cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

This paper is about end-to-end speech recognition using deep neural network models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and speech recognition. The paper also discusses the problem of overfitting and the need to separate essential factors for speech recognition from nuisances, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SD (Sound), which deals with audio and speech processing. The paper proposes an unsupervised adversarial invariance induction framework, which involves machine learning and could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
